  "body": "As seen [in the forum](https://forum.openzeppelin.com/t/strings-tostring-only-works-with-statically-defined-uint256-and-fails-otherwise/36514/2), `Strings.toString(1)` does not compile in 4.9.0 because `1` could be a signed or unsigned integer and `toString` is available for signed integers since https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/pull/3773.\r\n\r\nWe might want to rename the function to `toStringSigned` so that the basic `toString` function can be used with integer literals.",
